messages.content: What is the purpose of the extended-saveimage-comfyui custom node?
The extended-saveimage-comfyui custom node allows saving images in JPEG and WEBP formats, in addition to the usual formats supported by the standard Save Image node in ComfyUI.
What types of compression does the extended-saveimage-comfyui node support for WEBP format?
The extended-saveimage-comfyui node supports both lossless and lossy compression for the WEBP format.
Does the extended-saveimage-comfyui node embed metadata in the saved images?
Yes, the extended-saveimage-comfyui node embeds metadata in the saved images as usual.
Can the images saved using the extended-saveimage-comfyui node be used to load a workflow in ComfyUI?
Yes, the images saved using the extended-saveimage-comfyui node can be used to load a workflow in ComfyUI.
How can I install the extended-saveimage-comfyui custom node?

To install the extended-saveimage-comfyui custom node, clone the repository into the `ComfyUI/custom_nodes` folder using the command `git clone https://github.com/palant/extended-saveimage-comfyui` and restart ComfyUI.
Is the extended-saveimage-comfyui custom node identical to the usual Save Image node?
The extended-saveimage-comfyui custom node is largely identical to the usual Save Image node, with the added functionality of saving images in JPEG and WEBP formats.
Does the extended-saveimage-comfyui custom node replace the existing Save Image node in ComfyUI?
No, the extended-saveimage-comfyui custom node does not replace the existing Save Image node. It is an additional custom node that provides extended functionality.
